---
export const prerender = true;
import StudioLegalLayout from "../layouts/StudioLegalLayout.astro";
---

<StudioLegalLayout
  title="Privacy — MOSION Studio"
  description="Privacy policy for MOSION Studio covering the Studio landing page and the Studio web app on studio.mosion.app — how we collect, use, share, and protect partner data."
  canonical="https://studio.mosion.app/privacy"
  pageLabel="Privacy"
>
  <article class="policy-article" aria-labelledby="privacyTitle">
    <header class="policy-intro">
      <h1 class="hero-title" id="privacyTitle">Privacy</h1>
      <div class="policy-meta">Updated June 13, 2026</div>
      <p class="hero-copy">
        This Privacy Policy explains how MOSION collects, uses, shares, and protects personal information through MOSION Studio — our platform for filmmakers, distributors, and rights holders. It covers the Studio landing page, the Studio application flow, and the Studio web app on <span class="inline-code">studio.mosion.app</span>. For the MOSION consumer service (the public site, web app, and mobile app), see <a class="contact-link" href="https://www.mosion.app/privacy">mosion.app/privacy</a>.
      </p>
      <ul class="policy-summary" aria-label="Privacy at a glance">
        <li>We collect what we need to review applications, run partner accounts, manage your titles, and report earnings.</li>
        <li>We do not sell your personal information.</li>
        <li>Studio is a professional platform, not a consumer app — it is not directed to children.</li>
        <li>You can access, correct, export, or delete your information by contacting us.</li>
      </ul>
      <ul class="policy-toc" aria-label="Privacy policy contents">
        <li><a href="#scope">01 Scope</a></li>
        <li><a href="#information">02 Information We Collect</a></li>
        <li><a href="#use">03 How We Use Information</a></li>
        <li><a href="#lawful-basis">04 Legal Bases</a></li>
        <li><a href="#sharing">05 How We Share</a></li>
        <li><a href="#content">06 Titles, Screeners And Content</a></li>
        <li><a href="#earnings">07 Earnings And Reporting</a></li>
        <li><a href="#device">08 Cookies And Storage</a></li>
        <li><a href="#retention">09 Retention</a></li>
        <li><a href="#transfers">10 International Transfers</a></li>
        <li><a href="#security">11 Security</a></li>
        <li><a href="#rights">12 Your Choices And Rights</a></li>
        <li><a href="#children">13 Children</a></li>
        <li><a href="#changes">14 Changes</a></li>
        <li><a href="#contact">15 Contact</a></li>
      </ul>
    </header>

    <section class="policy-section" id="scope" aria-labelledby="scopeHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">01 Scope</div>
      <h2 id="scopeHeading">What this page covers</h2>
      <p>This policy covers personal information processed through MOSION Studio: the Studio landing page, the Studio partner application form, and the Studio web app on <span class="inline-code">studio.mosion.app</span>. Studio is a professional platform for filmmakers, distributors, and rights holders who supply titles to MOSION.</p>
      <p>It does not cover the MOSION consumer service used by viewers — for that, see <a class="contact-link" href="https://www.mosion.app/privacy">mosion.app/privacy</a>. It also does not cover third parties whose services you reach through Studio, which operate under their own privacy policies.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="information" aria-labelledby="informationHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">02 Information We Collect</div>
      <h2 id="informationHeading">Information we collect</h2>
      <p>What we collect depends on how you interact with Studio. Some information you give us directly, some is created as you use the platform, and some technical information is processed automatically to operate, secure, and improve the service.</p>

      <div class="policy-subhead">Application information</div>
      <p>When you apply for MOSION Studio access, you may provide your first and last name, email address, website or portfolio URL, company name, your slate or lead-title information, applicant type, rights status, release stage, territory focus, a trailer or screener URL, and any submission summary or supporting context you choose to include.</p>

      <div class="policy-subhead">Account, authentication, and profile information</div>
      <p>When you sign in to the Studio web app, request a password reset, restore a session, or manage your profile, we process your email address, your password (stored only as a salted hash — never in readable form), authentication and session status, sign-in provider information, and profile details such as your first and last name, producer or studio name, title, phone number, website, and studio biography.</p>

      <div class="policy-subhead">Organisation and rights-holder information</div>
      <p>We may process information about your organisation, studio, distribution relationship, or rights-holder status, and the agreements and arrangements that govern your participation, where this is needed to review access, administer partner accounts, and operate Studio workflows.</p>

      <div class="policy-subhead">Title, content, and submission information</div>
      <p>When you submit or manage titles, we process the metadata, assets, screeners, trailers, and content you provide, together with their publication status and the settings you configure. This is described further under "Titles, screeners and content."</p>

      <div class="policy-subhead">Earnings and transaction information</div>
      <p>To report your performance on MOSION, we process records of sales of your titles, the applicable revenue split, and the resulting earnings and reporting figures shown in your Studio dashboard. This is described further under "Earnings and reporting."</p>

      <div class="policy-subhead">Communications and support information</div>
      <p>When you contact us, respond to a message, or use in-platform notifications and messaging, we process the contents of your communication, your contact details, and related metadata so we can respond and keep records of partner and support interactions.</p>

      <div class="policy-subhead">Device and technical information</div>
      <p>Hosting, infrastructure, and security systems may process technical information such as browser or device details, operating system, IP-related request data, timestamps, page requests, error and diagnostic events, and session-validation or abuse-prevention data associated with use of the platform.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="use" aria-labelledby="usageHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">03 How We Use Information</div>
      <h2 id="usageHeading">How we use information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To review Studio applications and determine whether a filmmaker, distributor, or rights holder is a fit for the platform.</li>
        <li>To create, authenticate, maintain, and secure Studio accounts and sessions.</li>
        <li>To provide partner tools — profile management, title submission and management, uploads, dashboards, earnings reporting, and notifications.</li>
        <li>To ingest, process, and publish the titles and assets you supply, and to make them available to viewers on the MOSION consumer service.</li>
        <li>To calculate, display, and account for sales, revenue splits, and earnings related to your titles.</li>
        <li>To communicate about applications, approvals, onboarding, sign-in, password resets, support issues, and policy or product changes.</li>
        <li>To monitor, troubleshoot, secure, and maintain the reliability of the landing page and the Studio web app, including diagnostics.</li>
        <li>To protect MOSION, our users, and our partners against fraud, abuse, unauthorised access, and legal claims, including rate limiting and content protection.</li>
        <li>To comply with applicable legal, contractual, tax, accounting, regulatory, and enforcement obligations.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="lawful-basis" aria-labelledby="basisHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">04 Legal Bases</div>
      <h2 id="basisHeading">Legal bases and equivalent grounds for processing</h2>
      <p>Where data protection law requires a legal basis, MOSION may rely on one or more of the following depending on the activity: performing our contract or partner relationship with you; taking steps at your request before entering into that relationship, such as reviewing your application; our legitimate interests in operating, securing, improving, and protecting the platform against fraud and abuse; complying with legal obligations such as tax and accounting; and your consent where a specific activity is offered on that basis. Where we rely on consent, you can withdraw it at any time without affecting processing already carried out.</p>
      <p>If local law gives you additional rights tied to a particular lawful basis, those rights may be available depending on your location and the nature of the processing involved.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="sharing" aria-labelledby="sharingHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">05 How We Share</div>
      <h2 id="sharingHeading">How information may be shared</h2>
      <p><strong>We do not sell your personal information.</strong> We share it only as described below.</p>
      <div class="policy-subhead">Service providers who help us run Studio</div>
      <p>We share personal information with vendors that process it on our behalf to operate the platform, under contracts that limit how they may use it — including providers supporting hosting and application delivery, authentication, databases, content storage and delivery, email delivery, error monitoring, and security operations.</p>
      <div class="policy-subhead">Across the MOSION service</div>
      <p>Information you supply about your titles — and the assets and metadata for them — is used to publish those titles to viewers on the MOSION consumer service. Aggregated or partner-facing performance information may be shown to you in your dashboard. We do not expose your private account, contact, or organisation details to viewers.</p>
      <div class="policy-subhead">Legal, safety, and business transfers</div>
      <p>We may disclose information where reasonably necessary to comply with law, respond to lawful requests, enforce our terms or agreements, protect the rights, property, or safety of MOSION, our users, or our partners, investigate abuse or security incidents, or support a financing, restructuring, merger, acquisition, or asset transfer involving the service.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="content" aria-labelledby="contentHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">06 Titles, Screeners And Content</div>
      <h2 id="contentHeading">Titles, screeners, and content you submit</h2>
      <p>When you apply or onboard, and as you manage your catalogue, you may submit titles together with metadata, artwork, trailers, screeners, and the film content itself, along with the publication and access settings you configure. We process and store this to review your submission, ingest and protect your content, publish approved titles, and operate the consumer playback experience.</p>
      <p>Content delivery and digital-rights-management providers help us store, secure, and deliver this material. Published films are protected by digital rights management on the consumer service so that only viewers who have purchased access can watch them. You are responsible for ensuring you hold the rights to the materials and personal information you submit and for the lawful basis for any third-party personal information they contain.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="earnings" aria-labelledby="earningsHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">07 Earnings And Reporting</div>
      <h2 id="earningsHeading">Earnings and reporting</h2>
      <p>To show how your titles perform, we process records of consumer purchases of those titles, apply the revenue split that governs your relationship, and present the resulting earnings and reporting figures in your Studio dashboard. We retain the underlying transaction and accounting records for as long as required by tax, accounting, and legal obligations.</p>
      <p>Consumer payments are handled by our payment providers on the consumer service; MOSION does not receive or store viewers' full payment credentials, and those details are not exposed to Studio partners. Where settlement of your earnings is arranged, any banking or payout details you provide are used only to administer that payment.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="device" aria-labelledby="deviceHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">08 Cookies And Storage</div>
      <h2 id="deviceHeading">Cookies and local storage</h2>
      <p>The Studio landing page and web app use cookies and similar browser storage (such as local storage) to keep you signed in, remember your preferences, operate core features, and support security and performance. We do not use cookies or storage to sell your information or to build cross-site advertising profiles. You can manage browser storage through your browser settings, though clearing essential storage will sign you out and may break parts of the platform. See our <a class="contact-link" href="https://studio.mosion.app/cookies">Cookies policy</a> for more detail.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="retention" aria-labelledby="retentionHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">09 Retention</div>
      <h2 id="retentionHeading">Retention and user control</h2>
      <p>We keep personal information for as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this policy, then delete or anonymise it. Retention varies by data type:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Application records may be retained for review, relationship management, support, and compliance purposes, including where an application is not approved.</li>
        <li>Account, profile, and organisation information is kept while your partner relationship is active and for a reasonable period after closure where needed for support, security, or legal obligations.</li>
        <li>Title, content, and submission materials are kept while your titles are listed or as needed to operate, account for, and support them.</li>
        <li>Earnings, transaction, and accounting records are kept for the periods required by tax, accounting, and legal obligations.</li>
        <li>Diagnostic, security, and abuse-prevention data is kept for limited periods appropriate to those purposes.</li>
        <li>Cookies and local-storage entries persist for the periods set by the relevant store unless cleared earlier by sign-out or your browser controls.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="transfers" aria-labelledby="transferHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">10 International Transfers</div>
      <h2 id="transferHeading">International transfers</h2>
      <p>MOSION and the providers that support it may process information in more than one country, which may have different data protection laws than your own. When information is transferred across borders, we aim to use reasonable contractual, organisational, and technical safeguards appropriate to the service and transfer involved to protect it in line with this policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="security" aria-labelledby="securityHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">11 Security</div>
      <h2 id="securityHeading">Security</h2>
      <p>We use technical, administrative, and organisational measures designed to protect personal information and account access — including encrypted transport, hashed passwords, access controls, content protection for the films you supply, and rate limiting and monitoring against abuse. No online service, storage environment, or transmission method can be guaranteed to be completely secure, so you should also take reasonable care with your own credentials and devices, and contact us if you believe your account has been compromised.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="rights" aria-labelledby="rightsHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">12 Your Choices And Rights</div>
      <h2 id="rightsHeading">Your choices and rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on the law that applies to you, you may have rights to request access to your personal information, correction of inaccurate information, deletion, restriction, objection, portability, or withdrawal of consent where processing is based on consent. You can exercise these rights, or ask questions about them, by contacting us — we may need to verify your identity before acting on a request.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>You can update some profile information directly inside the Studio web app.</li>
        <li>You can clear browser cookies and local storage using your browser controls.</li>
        <li>You can request deletion of your account and associated personal information, subject to records we must keep for legal, tax, contractual, or fraud-prevention reasons, and to obligations connected to titles you have published.</li>
        <li>You may also have the right to lodge a complaint with a relevant privacy or data protection regulator in your jurisdiction.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>MOSION does not sell personal information and does not use it for cross-context behavioural advertising.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="children" aria-labelledby="childrenHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">13 Children</div>
      <h2 id="childrenHeading">Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>MOSION Studio is a professional platform intended for filmmakers, distributors, and rights holders. It is not directed to, or intended for use by, children, and we do not knowingly collect personal information from children through Studio. If you believe a child has provided personal information to Studio, contact us and we will take reasonable steps to review and remove it where required.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="changes" aria-labelledby="changesHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">14 Changes</div>
      <h2 id="changesHeading">Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in product features, data practices, legal requirements, or operational needs. When we do, we will update the date at the top of this page and publish the revised version here. For significant changes, we may provide additional notice through the platform. Your continued use of MOSION Studio after an update takes effect means you accept the revised policy.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section" id="contact" aria-labelledby="contactHeading">
      <div class="policy-section-label">15 Contact</div>
      <h2 id="contactHeading">Questions</h2>
      <p>For Studio privacy questions, or to exercise your rights, contact <a class="contact-link" href="mailto:partners@mosion.app">partners@mosion.app</a>. For the MOSION consumer service, see <a class="contact-link" href="https://www.mosion.app/privacy">mosion.app/privacy</a>.</p>
    </section>
  </article>
</StudioLegalLayout>
